	 Xbox 360 defies definition as a gaming device 
	 The newest and possibly snazziest of gaming systems that made its debut at the market place this week - the Xbox 360, also happens to be a box of home networking tools. And its $400 price tag did not deter fans from queuing overnight or braving the cold to just get their palms on the easy-to-covet Microsoft console. 
